  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a prospective observational registry of clinical pump deployments in which hemolysis indices were measured under routine operative conditions. The registry data are cited throughout the assessment narrative as providing experimental grounding for the CFD predictions, and the comparison of RH values against predicate device benchmarks is described as fulfilling the controlled-experiment requirement stipulated in the validation plan. The breadth of patient-flow-speed combinations captured in the registry (n=312 cases spanning 3–6 L/min, 2500–4500 RPM) is presented as equivalent in evidentiary weight to a purpose-designed bench experiment.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
