      "name": "Hemolysis index validation against CPB clinical registry (RH < 1 across all 5 operating points)",
      "description": "CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) values were compared against hemolysis measurements drawn from the CPB clinical outcomes registry (n=312 cases). Across all five target flow-speed operating points, CFD predictions yielded RH < 1 relative to the predicate device benchmark, satisfying the acceptance criterion. The registry encompasses patients undergoing elective cardiac surgery at three centres; plasma-free haemoglobin was measured at standardised intervals. The breadth and clinical representativeness of the registry data are considered to provide robust experimental grounding for the CFD validation, and the comparison is described in the assessment narrative as fulfilling the requirement for experimental confirmation of model predictions.",
      "passFail": "Pass",
      "acceptanceCriterion": "RH < 1.0 for all five flow-speed combinations",
